		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Extensible Metadata Platform</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Xmp_tagline_200px.png" class="image" title="XMP logo"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/ad/Xmp_tagline_200px.png/180px-Xmp_tagline_200px.png" width="180" height="73" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Xmp_tagline_200px.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
XMP logo</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The Adobe <b>Extensible Metadata Platform</b> (<b>XMP</b>) is a standard for processing and storing standardized and proprietary metadata, created by <a href="/wiki/ADBE" title="ADBE" class="mw-redirect">Adobe Systems Inc.</a>.</p>
<p>XMP standardizes the definition, creation, and processing of extensible <a href="/wiki/Metadata" title="Metadata">metadata</a>. Serialized XMP can be embedded into a significant number of popular file formats, without breaking their readability by non-XMP-aware applications. Embedding metadata ("the truth is in the file") avoids many problems that occur when metadata is stored separately. XMP is used in <a href="/wiki/Portable_Document_Format" title="Portable Document Format">PDF</a>, <a href="/wiki/Photography" title="Photography">photography</a> and <a href="/wiki/Graphics_software" title="Graphics software">photo editing</a> applications.</p>
